# Dataset Sources

This project uses data from the following sources:

## 1. Oceanic Niño Index (ONI)

Source: NOAA Climate Prediction Center

https://origin.cpc.ncep.noaa.gov/products/analysis_monitoring/ensostuff/ONI_v5.php

Description:
The Oceanic Niño Index (ONI) is used to identify El Niño and La Niña events based on sea surface temperature anomalies.

---

## 2. ERA5 Reanalysis Dataset

Source: Copernicus Climate Data Store

https://cds.climate.copernicus.eu/

Variables Used:
- Temperature (t)
- Relative Humidity (r)
- Specific Humidity (q)
- Geopotential Height (z)
- Wind Components (u, v, w)

Pressure Level:
- 850 hPa

Region:
- Latitude: 30°N to 30°S
- Longitude: 120°E to 280°E

---

## Note

The complete ERA5 dataset is not included in this repository due to its large size.
Users can download the data directly from the Copernicus Climate Data Store.
